Hey, what about Spock?
You know him too?

580
00:31:09,118 --> 00:31:12,453
I've met Leonard Nimoy
but I wouldn't say we're friends.

581
00:31:12,496 --> 00:31:14,664
And for that matter, George and I

582
00:31:14,707 --> 00:31:17,083
aren't on the best of terms
at the moment, I'm afraid.

583
00:31:17,126 --> 00:31:19,627
Mr. Howard, have you
ever been married?

584
00:31:19,670 --> 00:31:22,171
No, I've never met
the right little lady.

585
00:31:22,214 --> 00:31:24,007
Yeah, right.

586
00:31:24,049 --> 00:31:27,844
As Shirley MacLaine said,
"True love is supposed to be rare.

587
00:31:27,887 --> 00:31:29,095
That's how we know
it's valuable."

588
00:31:29,138 --> 00:31:30,680
That's beautiful.

589
00:31:30,723 --> 00:31:32,473
Shirley's actually a client of ours.

590
00:31:32,516 --> 00:31:33,808
She is a very nice woman.

591
00:31:33,851 --> 00:31:36,060
You know Shirley MacLaine?

592
00:31:36,103 --> 00:31:39,188
That's what I do. I arrange and
coordinate publicity for celebrities.

593
00:31:39,231 --> 00:31:40,899
- Well, give us some dirt!
- No!

594
00:31:40,941 --> 00:31:43,026
We want to know
who's sleeping with who!

595
00:31:43,068 --> 00:31:45,570
- I take the fifth because...
- I know Shirley. She...

596
00:31:45,613 --> 00:31:47,864
- I cannot say anything complimentary.
- She came to a show I did.

597
00:31:47,907 --> 00:31:49,324
All right, tell us who's nice, then.

598
00:31:49,366 --> 00:31:52,452
Okay. Um, so,

599
00:31:52,494 --> 00:31:54,537
people like to make fun
of Keanu Reeves,

600
00:31:54,580 --> 00:31:56,539
right, 'cause he's...

601
00:31:56,582 --> 00:31:58,958
but he is one of the sweetest
guys you will ever meet.

602
00:31:59,001 --> 00:32:01,002
Oh, you can tell that.

603
00:32:01,045 --> 00:32:03,129
Tell him he kicked butt
in "The Matrix"!

604
00:32:03,172 --> 00:32:04,756
- Tell him.
- Okay.

605
00:32:04,798 --> 00:32:06,591
Um, and, um, Jay Leno...

606
00:32:08,052 --> 00:32:09,802
he's just a regular guy
from Boston.

607
00:32:09,845 --> 00:32:13,014
Just really down to earth,
really sweet.

608
00:32:13,057 --> 00:32:14,849
You think Jay Leno is

609
00:32:14,892 --> 00:32:18,895
just a regular sweet guy
from Boston?

610
00:32:18,938 --> 00:32:22,732
You don't have the slightest idea
what you're talking about.

611
00:32:24,109 --> 00:32:26,861
Well, I met Jay Leno
a number of times

612
00:32:26,904 --> 00:32:29,155
and he's always
been really warm.

613
00:32:29,198 --> 00:32:30,698
Then he was faking.

614
00:32:30,741 --> 00:32:34,160
I know Jay Leno, missy.
I know him.

615
00:32:34,203 --> 00:32:35,995
I've dealt with Jay Leno.

616
00:32:36,038 --> 00:32:38,915
- You'll have to trust me on this one.
- I...

617
00:32:45,047 --> 00:32:47,090
Buck Howard?
To makeup.

618
00:32:48,884 --> 00:32:50,843
No, Buck. This way.

619
00:32:50,886 --> 00:32:52,345
Let's do it!

620
00:32:54,306 --> 00:32:57,308
I'll be right back. I have to go
call and check in on the boys.

621
00:32:58,686 --> 00:33:03,022
She's great, my sister.

622
00:33:03,065 --> 00:33:05,024
She's a genius,

623
00:33:05,067 --> 00:33:09,195
very artistic, been married
a whole bunch of times.

624
00:33:09,238 --> 00:33:12,740
She's lived a glamorous life.

625
00:33:12,783 --> 00:33:14,909
Sounds like it.

626
00:33:17,454 --> 00:33:19,455
Hey.

627
00:33:20,958 --> 00:33:22,917
How does Buck do his tricks?

628
00:33:22,960 --> 00:33:25,420
I'm not gonna tell anyone, I swear.

629
00:33:25,462 --> 00:33:27,922
I don't know. I don't...

630
00:33:27,965 --> 00:33:31,092
You're his assistant.
He's got to tell you something.

631
00:33:31,135 --> 00:33:34,971
Kenny, as far as I know, it's real.

632
00:33:36,557 --> 00:33:38,266
Damn.

633
00:33:38,308 --> 00:33:40,685
They're gonna go to commercial
in a couple of minutes.

634
00:33:40,728 --> 00:33:42,353
Then we're on.

635
00:33:42,396 --> 00:33:45,356
The producer says
we can watch from the booth.

636
00:33:45,399 --> 00:33:47,108
Okay.

637
00:33:47,151 --> 00:33:50,570
You smell really nice.

638
00:33:53,157 --> 00:33:55,450
Thanks.

639
00:33:55,492 --> 00:33:57,452
Cindy Crown here,
back with magician Buck Howard,

640
00:33:57,494 --> 00:34:00,538
or the Great Buck Howard
as he's more commonly known.

641
00:34:00,581 --> 00:34:03,708
It is wonderful to have you
in Cincinnati, Buck.

642
00:34:03,751 --> 00:34:07,128
Thanks, Cindy.
I'm very glad to be here.

643
00:34:07,171 --> 00:34:10,590
Yes, and I understand
you're here for a very special show.

644
00:34:10,632 --> 00:34:12,133
That's correct, Cindy.

645
00:34:12,176 --> 00:34:13,801
On Saturday evening,

646
00:34:13,844 --> 00:34:16,304
I will be performing

647
00:34:16,346 --> 00:34:19,223
at the Cincinnati Arts Complex.

648
00:34:19,266 --> 00:34:22,310
I was afraid Ohio
may have an arts complex,

649
00:34:22,352 --> 00:34:24,645
but I never expected
it would be in Cincinnati.

650
00:34:25,856 --> 00:34:27,523
And on Sunday afternoon,

651
00:34:27,566 --> 00:34:30,318
I'll be staging
a very important event.

652
00:34:30,360 --> 00:34:31,944
Why don't you tell us about that?

653
00:34:34,573 --> 00:34:37,658
This has been top secret
to this very moment.

654
00:34:37,701 --> 00:34:41,662
At roughly 2:00 P.M.,

655
00:34:41,705 --> 00:34:43,831
I will put to sleep

656
00:34:43,874 --> 00:34:45,833
900 souls,

657
00:34:45,876 --> 00:34:49,337
whom I will wake up
immediately afterwards,

658
00:34:49,379 --> 00:34:52,298
as if from the dead.

659
00:34:52,341 --> 00:34:55,009
Well, that sounds just super.

660
00:34:55,052 --> 00:34:56,844
Be sure to come out
for both events, folks.

661
00:34:56,887 --> 00:34:59,430
Now, I've heard you're going
to do a warmup

662
00:34:59,473 --> 00:35:01,641
by performing
a magic trick on me.

663
00:35:01,683 --> 00:35:05,311
Take this piece of paper
in your left hand.

664
00:35:05,354 --> 00:35:07,355
I'll need a coin. Ah!

665
00:35:07,397 --> 00:35:08,856
Yes, there's one.

666
00:35:08,899 --> 00:35:10,691
Oh!

667
00:35:10,734 --> 00:35:15,113
I want you to hold
that silver dollar in your hand

668
00:35:15,155 --> 00:35:17,156
between your thumb
and your forefinger.

669
00:35:17,199 --> 00:35:19,325
I will begin counting.

670
00:35:19,368 --> 00:35:23,538
Whenever you feel compelled, all you
need to do is simply drop the coin.

671
00:35:23,580 --> 00:35:25,540
Ready?

672
00:35:25,582 --> 00:35:30,878
One, two,

673
00:35:30,921 --> 00:35:32,880
three,

674
00:35:32,923 --> 00:35:38,219
four.

675
00:35:40,222 --> 00:35:41,389
Five.

676
00:35:41,431 --> 00:35:43,182
- 20 seconds, Cindy.
- six.

677
00:35:43,225 --> 00:35:46,018
Cindy, you do understand
that at some point in time

678
00:35:46,061 --> 00:35:49,105
- you have to let the coin drop.
- Oh, I'm sorry.

679
00:35:49,148 --> 00:35:51,607
- Maybe I didn't understand.
- 10 seconds, Cindy.

680
00:35:51,650 --> 00:35:53,067
We're almost out of time.

681
00:35:53,110 --> 00:35:55,278
But we can do this
very quickly. Go ahead.

682
00:35:55,320 --> 00:35:58,322
Hold out your hand.
We'll try it one more time very quickly.

683
00:35:58,365 --> 00:36:00,241
Ready...

684
00:36:00,284 --> 00:36:02,577
- I'm sorry, we are out of time, Buck.
- Oh my God.

685
00:36:02,619 --> 00:36:05,454
- And thank you...
- Cut 'em off.

686
00:36:05,497 --> 00:36:08,583
- Let's don't drop the coin...
- We're out.

687
00:36:08,625 --> 00:36:11,294
Maybe you could come back
at some other point in the future.

688
00:36:12,921 --> 00:36:14,964
Listen, I'm sorry.
Mr. Howard...

689
00:36:20,554 --> 00:36:22,513
What the hell is wrong
with that guy?

690
00:36:22,556 --> 00:36:25,349
He won't pick up his phone
and I'm trying to apologize.

691
00:36:25,392 --> 00:36:28,603
I don't know what for,
but I am trying to apologize.

692
00:36:28,645 --> 00:36:31,230
It's okay. Just relax.

693
00:36:31,273 --> 00:36:33,232
Trust me.
This is what Buck is like.

694
00:36:33,275 --> 00:36:35,735
Tomorrow he'll act like
nothing happened.

695
00:36:35,777 --> 00:36:37,653
What are we doing here?

696
00:36:39,156 --> 00:36:40,948
I mean, seriously,

697
00:36:40,991 --> 00:36:42,742
how on earth does a guy like you

698
00:36:42,784 --> 00:36:44,202
wind up working with Buck Howard?

699
00:36:44,244 --> 00:36:46,704
- I want to know.
- I had just quit law school

700
00:36:46,747 --> 00:36:48,289
and moved to L.A.

701
00:36:48,332 --> 00:36:51,626
I bet you wish you'd just stayed in
school right about now.

702
00:36:51,668 --> 00:36:53,252
No way.

703
00:36:53,295 --> 00:36:56,005
Look, Buck is no picnic,

704
00:36:56,048 --> 00:36:58,799
but law school was...
oh my God.

705
00:36:58,842 --> 00:37:00,760
I would wake up every day there

706
00:37:00,802 --> 00:37:02,762
just dreading life.

707
00:37:02,804 --> 00:37:06,849
Look, I'll admit I have
no idea what I'm doing,

708
00:37:06,892 --> 00:37:09,644
and obviously I've got to
quit this job and figure it out,

709
00:37:09,686 --> 00:37:12,980
but I'm trying,

710
00:37:13,023 --> 00:37:14,982
and it feels good.

711
00:37:15,025 --> 00:37:17,151
It feels like what I'm supposed
to do, you know?

712
00:37:17,194 --> 00:37:20,029
Oh, come on.
You're not supposed to do anything.

713
00:37:20,072 --> 00:37:22,657
Life is not magical like that, okay?

714
00:37:22,699 --> 00:37:24,242
No one is supposed to do anything.

715
00:37:24,284 --> 00:37:26,202
How do you know that?

716
00:37:26,245 --> 00:37:28,996
'Cause it boils down
to the same thing for everyone,

717
00:37:29,039 --> 00:37:32,667
from Buck Howard
to Meryl Streep to you.

718
00:37:32,709 --> 00:37:36,754
Most creative people, they just want
the world to love and adore them,

719
00:37:36,797 --> 00:37:38,172
which is infantile.

720
00:37:38,215 --> 00:37:40,049
Okay, all right.

721
00:37:40,092 --> 00:37:43,886
Maybe I'm naive, but

722
00:37:43,929 --> 00:37:46,389
life is short,

723
00:37:46,431 --> 00:37:49,600
you know?
I mean, someday

724
00:37:49,643 --> 00:37:51,185
we're not gonna be here.

725
00:37:51,228 --> 00:37:53,604
And if that's the case,

726
00:37:53,647 --> 00:37:57,692
I want to spend the time
that I have doing something

727
00:37:57,734 --> 00:37:59,527
that makes my heart race.

728
00:37:59,569 --> 00:38:02,571
I don't care what
that says about me.

729
00:38:02,614 --> 00:38:04,657
It's how I feel.

730
00:38:06,368 --> 00:38:08,577
That really turns me on.

731
00:38:08,620 --> 00:38:11,706
Are you serious?

732
00:38:11,748 --> 00:38:15,918
Yeah. That whole existential thing...

733
00:38:18,714 --> 00:38:21,257
I have a boyfriend.

734
00:38:21,300 --> 00:38:23,342
Oh, forget I said it.

735
00:38:38,608 --> 00:38:40,985
- Hello?
- Troy, are you asleep?

736
00:38:41,028 --> 00:38:43,779
Buck, no, I'm awake.

737
00:38:43,822 --> 00:38:45,448
I just think I'm coming down
with something. What's up?

738
00:38:45,490 --> 00:38:47,450
Where the hell is Valerie?

739
00:38:47,492 --> 00:38:50,244
She's supposed to be
organizing interviews for me today.

740
00:38:50,287 --> 00:38:52,955
I have no idea where she is.

741
00:38:54,791 --> 00:38:57,710
I don't know where she is exactly,

742
00:38:57,753 --> 00:39:00,713
but I'm sure she's on top of it.

743
00:39:00,756 --> 00:39:02,423
I'll try and track her down.

744
00:39:02,466 --> 00:39:05,301
I was just on my way
to the theater right now.

745
00:39:05,344 --> 00:39:07,970
Well, I'll be in my room preparing
for the show tonight.

746
00:39:08,013 --> 00:39:11,015
I don't want to be disturbed
unless it's for press.

747
00:39:11,058 --> 00:39:13,559
Okay.

748
00:39:13,602 --> 00:39:16,270
Spotlight on me.
Buck will enter stage right,

749
00:39:16,313 --> 00:39:18,481
come up to the microphone...
"I love this town"...

750
00:39:18,523 --> 00:39:20,066
do a few effects.

751
00:39:20,108 --> 00:39:22,109
Eventually he will come
over to the piano.

