- We're really happy...

1248
01:08:10,170 --> 01:08:11,796
Now, ladies and gentlemen,

1249
01:08:11,838 --> 01:08:14,381
these two people
will come backstage with me

1250
01:08:14,424 --> 01:08:17,301
to keep an eye on me to make sure
there's no funny business,

1251
01:08:17,344 --> 01:08:21,514
and these two people
will hide my fee in cash

1252
01:08:21,556 --> 01:08:24,517
somewhere in this auditorium.

1253
01:08:24,559 --> 01:08:26,268
You have my fee.

1254
01:08:26,311 --> 01:08:28,270
All right, shall we?

1255
01:08:33,693 --> 01:08:36,278
Here we go. Man of the hour.

1256
01:08:36,321 --> 01:08:39,156
Great job, Buck.
It's going great.

1257
01:08:39,199 --> 01:08:41,992
Hey, Buck,
let me ask you something.

1258
01:08:42,035 --> 01:08:43,828
How do they work
this thing with your money?

1259
01:08:43,870 --> 01:08:45,204
What do you mean?

1260
01:08:45,247 --> 01:08:48,582
I assume the casino pays you
by the month, right?

1261
01:08:48,625 --> 01:08:50,584
So is that a week's
worth of cash out there?

1262
01:08:50,627 --> 01:08:52,920
- Honey, shh.
- What? I'm curious.

1263
01:08:52,963 --> 01:08:54,880
- Um...
- Excuse me. I'm sorry. Hi.

1264
01:08:54,923 --> 01:08:57,550
I work for the casinos, sir,
and it's a good question.

1265
01:08:57,592 --> 01:08:58,884
The agreement we have with Buck

1266
01:08:58,927 --> 01:09:00,678
is that if he's unable
to find the money,

1267
01:09:00,720 --> 01:09:02,972
a pro-rated sum
for tonight's show only,

1268
01:09:03,014 --> 01:09:05,808
it is deducted from his salary
and donated to charity.

1269
01:09:05,851 --> 01:09:09,311
Boring!

1270
01:09:09,354 --> 01:09:12,773
- They're ready for you.
- Mr. Howard...

1271
01:09:12,816 --> 01:09:15,151
- We're here to party.
- ...they're ready for you.

1272
01:09:15,193 --> 01:09:18,070
- Gotta get out there!
- Go get 'em, Buck!

1273
01:09:18,113 --> 01:09:20,406
As I went back
to watch him finish the show,

1274
01:09:20,448 --> 01:09:23,868
I had this feeling that
it was time for me to move on.

1275
01:09:23,910 --> 01:09:27,788
I was Buck's road manager,
and his days on the road were over.

1276
01:09:27,831 --> 01:09:30,374
Now for this next effect

1277
01:09:30,417 --> 01:09:32,835
I will need complete silence,

1278
01:09:32,878 --> 01:09:36,505
absolute concentration.
Thank you.

1279
01:09:38,466 --> 01:09:41,385
Two-year deal. Buck did it.

1280
01:09:41,428 --> 01:09:43,262
Yes, his show had changed...

1281
01:09:43,305 --> 01:09:45,389
the doves, the scarves...

1282
01:09:45,432 --> 01:09:48,142
but it seemed like Buck was okay
with these compromises.

1283
01:09:50,478 --> 01:09:54,231
And despite it all,
his show still came down to this,

1284
01:09:54,274 --> 01:09:56,233
his signature effect,

1285
01:09:56,276 --> 01:09:58,319
the thing he had
always been known for.

1286
01:10:13,335 --> 01:10:15,419
Gil, is he all right?

1287
01:10:15,462 --> 01:10:17,338
Oh, just fine.

1288
01:10:26,181 --> 01:10:29,642
But then, suddenly,

1289
01:10:29,684 --> 01:10:33,896
for the first time
in a nearly 40-year career,

1290
01:10:37,067 --> 01:10:38,984
Buck couldn't find his money.

1291
01:10:45,575 --> 01:10:49,870
And just like that, it was over.

1292
01:11:14,604 --> 01:11:16,647
So here you are.

1293
01:11:19,484 --> 01:11:21,902
What are you gonna do now, kid?

1294
01:11:23,488 --> 01:11:26,782
Well, um,

1295
01:11:26,825 --> 01:11:28,784
I've been doing some writing.

1296
01:11:28,827 --> 01:11:32,162
Really?
Like for a newspaper?

1297
01:11:32,205 --> 01:11:34,873
No, different kind of writing.

1298
01:11:34,916 --> 01:11:39,044
Oh. You mean the kind
where they don't pay you.

1299
01:11:39,087 --> 01:11:42,965
Well, I'm hoping eventually,
but so far, yeah.

1300
01:11:43,008 --> 01:11:46,010
You don't remember because
you were a little kid.

1301
01:11:46,052 --> 01:11:49,555
But your mom and I,
we barely made it in the beginning.

1302
01:11:49,597 --> 01:11:52,266
- we struggled...
- So that I wouldn't have to.

1303
01:11:52,309 --> 01:11:54,476
Yes, I know.

1304
01:11:54,519 --> 01:11:57,146
That's right.
But I didn't have a choice.

1305
01:11:57,188 --> 01:11:58,355
You do.

1306
01:11:58,398 --> 01:12:01,025
So, how about this...

1307
01:12:01,067 --> 01:12:05,070
you come back home,
you save up your money,

1308
01:12:05,113 --> 01:12:07,531
you go back to school...
hear me out, now,

1309
01:12:07,574 --> 01:12:08,907
just hear me out.

1310
01:12:08,950 --> 01:12:11,076
Entertainment law.

1311
01:12:11,119 --> 01:12:13,454
- Entertainment law.
- Dad, stop.

1312
01:12:13,496 --> 01:12:15,914
I wish I could
go back to school.

1313
01:12:15,957 --> 01:12:19,418
I know that if I do,
I'd be set, but I can't.

1314
01:12:19,461 --> 01:12:22,254
I have to try this.

1315
01:12:22,297 --> 01:12:24,256
It might be a crazy dream.

1316
01:12:24,299 --> 01:12:27,343
I might fail miserably,

1317
01:12:27,385 --> 01:12:30,763
but I have to at least try.

1318
01:12:30,805 --> 01:12:35,726
Otherwise, I'm not going
to be happy at anything.

1319
01:12:40,482 --> 01:12:42,483
Okay.

1320
01:12:44,402 --> 01:12:46,362
Good luck.

1321
01:12:46,404 --> 01:12:50,657
You are aware that the word
"writer" rarely appears

1322
01:12:50,700 --> 01:12:52,743
without the word
"starving" in front of it.

1323
01:12:54,412 --> 01:12:57,623
So you better finish
your breakfast.

1324
01:12:57,665 --> 01:12:59,625
And then take me
to the airport.

1325
01:12:59,667 --> 01:13:01,627
I gotta get out of Los Angeles.

1326
01:13:04,214 --> 01:13:07,299
My dad was right.
I did need to make money.

1327
01:13:07,342 --> 01:13:09,093
But I had learned from Buck

1328
01:13:09,135 --> 01:13:11,178
that when you do
the thing you love,

1329
01:13:11,221 --> 01:13:16,100
somehow, magically,
you find the money.

1330
01:13:25,360 --> 01:13:27,986
- Hi. Hi.
- Hi.

1331
01:13:28,029 --> 01:13:29,988
- How are you?
- I'm good.

1332
01:13:30,031 --> 01:13:33,325
Wow, so yeah,
that's Jonathan Finerman.

1333
01:13:33,368 --> 01:13:36,245
Yes, you remember him?
His show just got picked up

1334
01:13:36,287 --> 01:13:37,955
and we've just been doing press
round the clock.

1335
01:13:37,997 --> 01:13:40,833
I grew up watching him.
He was huge.

1336
01:13:40,875 --> 01:13:43,085
But I still don't understand

1337
01:13:43,128 --> 01:13:45,838
why he would want
to meet with me.

1338
01:13:45,880 --> 01:13:49,466
The writer's assistant got fired,
and I just mentioned you.

1339
01:13:49,509 --> 01:13:52,428
Troy, this could be
so great for you.

1340
01:13:52,470 --> 01:13:54,430
Most of the assistants,
they make staff in like a year or two.

1341
01:13:54,472 --> 01:13:56,348
It would be really good.

1342
01:13:56,391 --> 01:13:59,810
I don't usually do this sort of thing,
but I had to meet you.

1343
01:13:59,853 --> 01:14:02,938
You used to work
for Buck Howard.

1344
01:14:02,981 --> 01:14:05,816
Yeah, I did.

1345
01:14:05,859 --> 01:14:08,235
I've been a fan of his
ever since I was a kid.

1346
01:14:08,278 --> 01:14:11,113
I also do a little
amateur magic myself.

1347
01:14:11,156 --> 01:14:15,075
There's always been something
I've been curious about,

1348
01:14:15,118 --> 01:14:16,869
not that it matters...

1349
01:14:16,911 --> 01:14:18,454
I don't know how
he finds the money.

1350
01:14:18,496 --> 01:14:20,664
That's not what
I was gonna ask.

1351
01:14:20,707 --> 01:14:22,291
Is he gay?

1352
01:14:22,333 --> 01:14:24,293
I'm just wondering.

1353
01:14:24,335 --> 01:14:25,961
I don't know.

1354
01:14:26,004 --> 01:14:29,548
I never saw him with anyone, so...

1355
01:14:29,591 --> 01:14:31,758
Yeah, well...

1356
01:14:31,801 --> 01:14:34,678
the thing about the money,
I found that out. That's a total scam.

1357
01:14:35,680 --> 01:14:38,015
Really? How?

1358
01:14:38,057 --> 01:14:40,893
He wears an earpiece.

1359
01:14:40,935 --> 01:14:43,270
I've heard about this.

1360
01:14:43,313 --> 01:14:46,773
And there's a guy that travels with him
that tells him where the money is.

1361
01:14:46,816 --> 01:14:48,817
I think I would have noticed.

1362
01:14:48,860 --> 01:14:50,819
He travels separate.

1363
01:14:50,862 --> 01:14:52,988
No one is even sure what
the guy looks like.

1364
01:14:53,031 --> 01:14:54,406
He sees where the money is,

1365
01:14:54,449 --> 01:14:57,075
goes to the restroom
or out to his car...

1366
01:14:57,118 --> 01:14:59,161
only takes a second...

1367
01:14:59,204 --> 01:15:02,372
whispers into a microphone,
it goes right into Buck's ear.

1368
01:15:02,415 --> 01:15:06,418
"Third row,
lady in the green sweater."

1369
01:15:06,461 --> 01:15:08,795
And his job is done.

1370
01:15:11,424 --> 01:15:13,467
No, I don't believe it.

1371
01:15:15,970 --> 01:15:17,763
You're loyal. I like that.

1372
01:15:21,267 --> 01:15:24,603
Who would have thought
that Buck Howard on your resume

1373
01:15:24,646 --> 01:15:26,772
- would land you a job?
- Not me.

1374
01:15:26,814 --> 01:15:29,191
And seriously,
thank you very much

1375
01:15:29,234 --> 01:15:31,985
- for arranging this. It went very well.
- Come on.

1376
01:15:32,028 --> 01:15:34,071
So, thank you. I mean it.

1377
01:15:36,282 --> 01:15:39,993
Okay, well, I'm over here.

1378
01:15:42,330 --> 01:15:46,041
So, that boyfriend of yours,
how's that working out?

1379
01:15:46,084 --> 01:15:49,795
And you ask just because
you're concerned about my well-being?

1380
01:15:49,837 --> 01:15:52,422
Yes, of course.

1381
01:15:52,465 --> 01:15:53,674
Of course
I'm very very concerned.

1382
01:15:58,805 --> 01:16:00,180
I'll call you.

1383
01:16:00,223 --> 01:16:02,140
Okay.

1384
01:16:03,476 --> 01:16:06,061
Preferably late at night, drunk.

1385
01:16:06,104 --> 01:16:08,313
Always!

1386
01:16:08,356 --> 01:16:10,857
Okay. Bye.

1387
01:16:10,900 --> 01:16:14,528
And just like that,
I began a whole new life.

1388
01:16:14,571 --> 01:16:18,282
Still, I thought
about Buck all the time.

1389
01:16:18,324 --> 01:16:21,785
He had just disappeared
after that night in Vegas.

1390
01:16:21,828 --> 01:16:25,497
I wondered what
exactly had gone wrong.

1391
01:16:25,540 --> 01:16:28,333
Buck had never failed
to find his money before.

1392
01:16:28,376 --> 01:16:30,335
It didn't make sense.

1393
01:16:30,378 --> 01:16:33,130
But then again,
maybe it proved he was real.

1394
01:16:33,172 --> 01:16:35,048
'Cause when you think about it,

1395
01:16:35,091 --> 01:16:38,802
only something fake could
work 100% of the time.

1396
01:16:38,845 --> 01:16:41,513
Regardless, I just wished there was
some way I could know that he was okay,

1397
01:16:41,556 --> 01:16:45,267
maybe talk to him one more time.

1398
01:17:10,501 --> 01:17:12,044
Come in.

1399
01:17:17,675 --> 01:17:21,762
- Hey, Buck.
- Troy! My goodness!

1400
01:17:21,804 --> 01:17:26,141
- How are you?
- I brought you something.

1401
01:17:26,184 --> 01:17:29,603
Look at that. Brandy.
That's very kind of you.

1402
01:17:29,646 --> 01:17:31,605
What are you doing here?

1403
01:17:31,648 --> 01:17:34,191
Just thought I'd take a trip up,
check out the show.

1404
01:17:34,233 --> 01:17:36,735
Come in.

1405
01:17:36,778 --> 01:17:38,028
Buck, it's 30 minutes to showtime.

1406
01:17:38,071 --> 01:17:40,656
Troy, this is Russell,
my new road manager.

1407
01:17:40,698 --> 01:17:44,159
Russell, Troy used to have yourjob,
but Troy understood

1408
01:17:44,202 --> 01:17:46,870
the importance of not looking
like a bum on the job.

1409
01:17:48,539 --> 01:17:49,831
Your tie.

1410
01:17:49,874 --> 01:17:52,042
You're not in a bar.

1411
01:17:52,085 --> 01:17:54,878
Come back when it's five minutes
and I need some water.

1412
01:17:54,921 --> 01:17:56,880
Actually, there is
some water right there.

1413
01:17:56,923 --> 01:17:58,882
That's distilled water.
I'm not an iron.

1414
01:17:58,925 --> 01:18:02,094
I drink spring water, remember?

1415
01:18:02,136 --> 01:18:04,262
Thank you.

1416
01:18:06,599 --> 01:18:10,352
So, you've come out of retirement.

1417
01:18:10,395 --> 01:18:13,271
Oh, I'll never give up, Troy.

1418
01:18:15,316 --> 01:18:17,776
So, why are you here?

1419
01:18:20,655 --> 01:18:22,656
What happened in Vegas?

1420
01:18:22,699 --> 01:18:24,950
Did you blow it on purpose?

1421
01:18:24,992 --> 01:18:27,953
Because that is the only explanation
that I can think of.

1422
01:18:27,995 --> 01:18:29,955
I know you wear an earpiece

1423
01:18:29,997 --> 01:18:33,959
and you have someone
in the audience

1424
01:18:34,001 --> 01:18:35,919
who tells you
where the money is.

1425
01:18:35,962 --> 01:18:39,965
Troy, that thing about the earpiece
has been going around for years.

1426
01:18:40,007 --> 01:18:41,383
It's a rumor.
Do you want to check?

1427
01:18:41,426 --> 01:18:43,510
No, it doesn't matter.

1428
01:18:43,553 --> 01:18:44,761
It's not important.

1429
01:18:44,804 --> 01:18:47,013
Look, I get it. It is a show.

1430
01:18:47,056 --> 01:18:48,306
You are there to entertain.

1431
01:18:48,349 --> 01:18:50,308
I understand.

1432
01:18:50,351 --> 01:18:52,811
I just want to know,
for myself.

1433
01:18:52,854 --> 01:18:55,480
What happened in Vegas?

1434
01:18:57,024 --> 01:19:00,902
You know, I don't really belong

1435
01:19:00,945 --> 01:19:02,904
in Vegas anymore.

1436
01:19:02,947 --> 01:19:05,657
I belong in places like these.

1437
01:19:07,034 --> 01:19:11,037
I love what I do.
I love these towns.

1438
01:19:11,080 --> 01:19:13,206
I love these people.

1439
01:19:13,249 --> 01:19:15,959
And I would never
cheat them, ever.

1440
01:19:18,546 --> 01:19:20,922
Watch the show tonight.

1441
01:19:23,551 --> 01:19:26,845
Thank you,
ladies and gentlemen.

1442
01:19:26,888 --> 01:19:31,057
I can't tell you how delighted
I am to be back in Bakersfield.

1443
01:19:31,100 --> 01:19:33,143
I love this town!

1444
01:19:33,186 --> 01:19:35,479
As I settled in
to watch Buck's show,

1445
01:19:35,521 --> 01:19:37,773
it struck me

1446
01:19:37,815 --> 01:19:40,150
this was the first time
I was seeing it as an audience member.

1447
01:19:40,193 --> 01:19:43,195
I want you to take
this piece of paper...

1448
01:19:43,237 --> 01:19:44,946
And it was his old show.

1449
01:19:44,989 --> 01:19:46,990
The changes he had made
in Vegas were gone

1450
01:19:47,033 --> 01:19:48,325
as if they had never happened.

1451
01:19:48,367 --> 01:19:50,994
And somehow it felt right.

1452
01:19:51,037 --> 01:19:52,996
It was actually kind of
beautiful in a way.

1453
01:19:53,039 --> 01:19:54,873
...because I know
what the number is.

1454
01:19:54,916 --> 01:19:57,626
The number you have
written down is the number 77.

1455
01:19:57,668 --> 01:19:59,377
Is that correct?

1456
01:19:59,420 --> 01:20:01,046
Show the audience.

1457
01:20:01,088 --> 01:20:02,380
Isn't that wild?

1458
01:20:02,423 --> 01:20:06,301
What the world needs now

1459
01:20:06,344 --> 01:20:08,887
Is love, sweet love...

1460
01:20:08,930 --> 01:20:12,641
When I tap them
on their left shoulder,

1461
01:20:12,683 --> 01:20:17,395
they will be sound asleep
in their chairs.

1462
01:20:17,438 --> 01:20:21,316
Humpty Dumpty sat on a wall...

1463
01:20:21,359 --> 01:20:25,570
Humpty Dumpty had
a great fall...

1464
01:20:27,532 --> 01:20:29,282
As the show neared its finale,

1465
01:20:29,325 --> 01:20:32,536
I saw that Buck had actually
made one small change.

1466
01:20:32,578 --> 01:20:34,538
And this one was just for me.

1467
01:20:34,580 --> 01:20:37,415
For many years
there have been rumors

1468
01:20:37,458 --> 01:20:41,127
that I employ some sort
of listening device

1469
01:20:41,170 --> 01:20:43,380
to aid me with this effect.

1470
01:20:43,422 --> 01:20:46,925
I would like to address
those rumors tonight.

1471
01:20:46,968 --> 01:20:49,344
Is there a doctor in the house?

1472
01:20:49,387 --> 01:20:51,137
Oh, there are two.

1473
01:20:51,180 --> 01:20:53,473
May I ask you both to come
onstage, please?

1474
01:20:55,935 --> 01:20:59,271
Take these instruments.
Please look in my ears

1475
01:20:59,313 --> 01:21:02,440
and tell the public
if I have any kind

1476
01:21:02,483 --> 01:21:05,318
of listening device whatsoever.

1477
01:21:07,697 --> 01:21:09,239
It's all clear.

1478
01:21:09,282 --> 01:21:11,032
Thank you.

1479
01:21:11,075 --> 01:21:13,118
Now, to convince

1480
01:21:13,160 --> 01:21:17,163
even the most hardened skeptics,

1481
01:21:17,206 --> 01:21:21,626
I will also put
this hood over my head.

1482
01:21:21,669 --> 01:21:24,629
I will ask you all to clap in unison

1483
01:21:24,672 --> 01:21:28,133
while my fee is being rehidden

1484
01:21:28,175 --> 01:21:30,969
here in the auditorium.

1485
01:21:31,012 --> 01:21:34,222
And I am ready.

1486
01:21:51,616 --> 01:21:53,199
They're done.

1487
01:21:53,242 --> 01:21:54,826
Thank you.

1488
01:21:56,412 --> 01:21:58,747
Ladies and gentlemen,
members of the public,

1489
01:21:58,789 --> 01:22:02,417
I may have to inconvenience you
one more time.

1490
01:22:02,460 --> 01:22:06,338
I must have, please,
for this effect, complete silence.

1491
01:23:11,696 --> 01:23:14,155
I couldn't watch because I knew

1492
01:23:14,198 --> 01:23:17,242
Buck wasn't going
to find the money.

1493
01:23:21,664 --> 01:23:24,374
I could only guess

1494
01:23:24,417 --> 01:23:26,918
that whatever Buck
had used in the past,

1495
01:23:26,961 --> 01:23:31,589
whether it was an earpiece
or his own powers,

1496
